verbose_text: Conversely, the one-step processes, involving bFGF treatment only (DLN-N2-10d and N2-TR-10d), induced more Brn3a and/or Brn3b expression, indicating that bFGF had a positive effect on RGC generation other than RPC maintenance, and that B27 was more likely to motivate general neural cell growth instead of RGLCs.
